<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-04T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-04T19:00:00-05:00" n="240" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d240">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 657.119/230a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SAG1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-04T19:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 4, 1918—7 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>201. Department has been advised by British Ambassador that your
                                British colleague has been instructed as soon as you have received
                                similar instructions to present a note to the Norwegian Government
                                stating that “providing a satisfactory arrangement with the United
                                States and the Allies is concluded, Norway will receive rations
                                estimated to satisfy her legitimate requirements.”</p>
                            <p>Department and War Trade Board approve of these instructions and you
                                are authorized to communicate to the Norwegian Government the
                                substance thereof, provided you deem the present moment an opportune
                                one.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>